The paper deals with integer least-squares problems, which are commonly encountered in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The focus on sparsity also suggests a connection to the field of compressed sensing (cs.DS). The use of analytical expressions and simulations to analyze the algorithm's performance suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
